1)rvm info-Shows information for current ruby
2)rvm reset-remove default and current settings, exit the shell.
3)rvm install   - install one or many ruby versions
4)rvm upgrade   - install new ruby, copy gemsets, make gems pristine, remove old ruby
5)rvm reinstall - remove ruby, install it, make gems pristine
6)rvm uninstall - uninstall one or many ruby versions, leaves their sources
7)rvm remove    - uninstall one or many ruby versions and remove their sources
8)rvm gemdir -switches to the gem directory of current ruby
9)rvm implode-removes the rvm installation completely
10)rvm reload-reload rvm source itself

